cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with depth image super-resolution using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely category as the paper deals with improving the resolution of depth images, which are commonly used in computer graphics applications. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques to learn the mapping from low-resolution to high-resolution depth images. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses deep neural networks to learn the mapping from low-resolution to high-resolution depth images. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with improving the resolution of depth images, which are commonly used in multimedia applications such as virtual reality and augmented reality.
